    • Method Detail

      • start

        void start(Context context,
         java.lang.String appKey,
         java.lang.String senderId,
         boolean sessionTrackingEnabled,
         int sessionDurationInMinutes,
         java.lang.String logLevel,
         boolean logToFile)
        This method should be called on when the activity's onStart method is called. The method initializes the sdk if this is the first time it is called and updates it if it isn't.
        Parameters:
        context - The application's context.
        appKey - The appKey that should be used for initializing the sdk (should be null if you're using mce.properties).
        senderId - The gcm sender id (project id) that should be used for initializing the sdk (should be null if you're using mce.properties).
        sessionTrackingEnabled - true if session tracking should be enabled. false otherwise.
        sessionDurationInMinutes - The maximum duration that a session can continue while the activity is in the background.
        logLevel - The sdk log level (none, error, warn, info or verbose)
        logToFile - true if logging will be saved in a log file or false foe no save.
